<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,265,291]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="184.[189,732,312,373]" box="[234,298,312,338]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,312,338]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="184.[189,732,312,373]" box="[189,732,347,373]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
LENGTH. Body 
<quantity box="[362,506,347,373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.15" metricValueMax="7.4" metricValueMin="6.9" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" unit="mm" value="7.15" valueMax="7.4" valueMin="6.9">6.9–7.4 mm</quantity>
, 5.3–5.9 wing mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="184.[189,1399,412,649]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
HEAD. Face in lateral view concave, strongly projected antero-ventrally; frontal prominence strongly developed. Ratio width of vertex at anterior ocellus: width of head 1: 3.7–4.2; ratio width of ocellar triangle: width of vertex 1: 1.8–2.1; ratio length of ocellar triangle: length of frons 1: 2.1–2.3. Face entirely yellow (as in 
<typeStatus box="[450,555,518,544]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">holotype</typeStatus>
) to predominantly black. Gena and mouth edge yellow, pale pollinose, with large subtriangular non-pollinose shiny area. Frons sub-shiny, slightly grey pollinose with wide but weak medial furrow (
<figureCitation box="[483,580,588,614]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="170.[189,232,1821,1847]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,457,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@170.[189,1399,457,1781]" captionTargetPageId="170" captionText="Fig. 88. Head. lateral view (C, E, F, J) and dorsal view (A–B, D, G–I, K–L). A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) spathigera sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Philippines. B–C. S. (A.) spenceri sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. D–E. S. (A.) strigillata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. F. S. (A.) tricoloripes, Brunetti, 1915, ♀, India. G. S. (A.) tricoloripes, Ƌ, India. H. S. (A.) umbrosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. I. S. (A.) varidissima Shiraki, 1930, Ƌ, Taiwan. J. S. (A.) varidissima, ♀, Taiwan. K. S. (A.) verrucosa sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. L. S. (A.) vietnamensis sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830732" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830732/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Fig. 88I</figureCitation>
). Scape and pedicel yellow or black. Basoflagellomere black squarish, ratio width: length 1: 1.0–1.1; arista short pilose basally; about 3.5 times as long as basoflagellomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="184.[189,1399,689,891]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
THORAX. Colour from dark brown to black to predominantly yellow, pollinose, scutum dark with more densely grey pollinose submedial vitta or scutum yellow with 3 shiny black vittae. Pleuron entirely yellow to predominantly black; posterior margin of katepisternum widely non-pollinose, shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1385,759,785]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="133.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1084,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@133.[189,1399,1084,1890]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="Fig. 65. Pleuron, lateral view. A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) crinita sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Java, Indonesia. B. S. (A.) dentata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Taiwan. C. S. (A.) nigerrima Shiraki, 1930, Ƌ, Taiwan. D. S. (A.) varidissima Shiraki, 1930, Ƌ, Taiwan. Scale bars 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830686/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Fig. 65D</figureCitation>
). Scutellum semicircular, black, with posterior margin narrowly pollinose, rest non-pollinose and shiny, long pilose, with two widely set long setae medially at posterior margin, ratio length of scutellum: length of seta 1: 1.8–2.0.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830754" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3830754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830754/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" startId="184.[189,232,1928,1954]" targetBox="[191,1395,932,1880]" targetPageId="184">
<paragraph blockId="184.[189,1399,1928,2024]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,282,1928,1954]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Fig. 94.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Shiraki, 1930" authorityName="Shiraki" authorityYear="1930" box="[290,899,1928,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varidissima" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[290,730,1928,1954]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) varidissima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shiraki T." box="[738,899,1928,1954]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" pagination="1" refId="ref92645" refString="Shiraki T. 1930. Die Syrphiden des japanischen Kaiserreichs, mit Berucksichtigung benachbarter Gebiete. Memoirs of the Faculty of Sciences and Agriculture 1 (1), Taihoku Imperial University, Formosa." type="journal article" year="1930">Shiraki, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
