<emphasis bold="true" box="[1183,1204,1963,1989]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">C</emphasis>
. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="185.[189,1398,266,328]" pageId="185" pageNumber="186">WING. Microtrichose, cell cup with basal 1/10 slightly microtrichose, almost bare; hyaline, stigma yellowish. Crossvein dm-cu meeting vein M obliquely and vein M</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[969,978,321,335]" pageId="185" pageNumber="186">1</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="185.[189,1398,266,328]" box="[985,1165,302,328]" pageId="185" pageNumber="186">meeting vein R</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[1165,1191,321,335]" pageId="185" pageNumber="186">4+5</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="185.[189,1398,266,328]" box="[1199,1389,302,328]" pageId="185" pageNumber="186">perpendicularly.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="185.[189,1398,367,499]" pageId="185" pageNumber="186">
LEGS. Colour yellow. Pro- and mesotibia dark yellow; pro- and mesobasitarsus dark brown, other tarsomeres dark brown to black. Metaleg, 
<figureCitation box="[666,767,402,428]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="185.[189,232,1891,1917]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,743,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@185.[189,1399,743,1852]" captionTargetPageId="185" captionText="Fig. 95. Metaleg, anterior view. A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) plautus sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. B. S. (A.) setosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Nepal. C. S. (A.) strigillata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. D. S. (A.) umbrosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. E. S. (A.) varidissima Shiraki, 1930, Ƌ, Taiwan, yellow form. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830756/files/figure.png" pageId="185" pageNumber="186">Fig. 95E</figureCitation>
, with coxa and trochanter yellow; femur predominantly yellow or biannulate, slightly incrassate, ratio width: length 1: 4.1–4.3; tibia black and yellow biannulate, without apical dens; tarsus with basitarsomere thin, ratio width: length 1: 3.8–4.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="185.[189,1399,538,670]" pageId="185" pageNumber="186">
ABDOMEN. Length ratio of terga I: II: III: IV 1: 3.8–4.1: 1.8–2.2: 1.2–1.4; ratio width at posterior margin: medial length of tergum II and III 1: 3.5–3.9 and 1: 1.0–1.1. Tergum III black with sub-anterior fascia covering 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[298,320,609,635]" italics="true" pageId="185" pageNumber="186">⅓</emphasis>
of the tergum; pile pale, on terga short, laterally on terga I and II long; tergum I with oblique row of 4–5 light yellow setae laterally; sternum III rectangular, ratio width: length 1: 2.5–2.7; sternum
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830756" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3830756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830756/files/figure.png" pageId="185" pageNumber="186" startId="185.[189,232,1891,1917]" targetBox="[189,1398,743,1851]" targetPageId="185">
